"title": "4221: cistern",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4221: cistern",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A reservoir for storing water collected from rainfall or from a spring. When empty, it was used for a variety of purposes. The word is also employed in a figurative sense.</p>\n<h2>Cisterns were used to collect water</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:10\">2CH 26:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:31\">2KI 18:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:16\">ISA 36:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:3\">JER 14:3</a></p>\n<h2>Other uses for cisterns</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:6-Jer38:13\">JER 38:6–38:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:19-Gen37:24\">GEN 37:19–37:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:28-Gen37:30\">GEN 37:28–37:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer41:4-Jer41:7\">JER 41:4–41:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer41:9\">JER 41:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:11\">ZEC 9:11</a></p>\n<h2>Cisterns used as symbols</h2>\n<h3>Cisterns as symbols of spiritual well-being</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:13\">JER 2:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Cisterns as symbols of physical well-being</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:15-Prov5:19\">PRO 5:15–5:19</a></p>",
